576
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:23,400
things wouldn’t have turned out this way.

577
00:34:25,679 --> 00:34:28,280
Though our business is already back on track,

578
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,440
Phum’s feelings aren’t the same anymore.

579
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:35,040
The moment he returned from abroad,

580
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:37,639
I could still remember the look in his eyes clearly.

581
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:41,360
It has remained my trauma until today.

582
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:44,280
What should I do, Tan?

583
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:50,159
Babe, don’t overthink it

584
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:54,520
because you’ve done your best all this time.

585
00:34:56,320 --> 00:35:02,400
I think Phum already knows his brother loves him the most.

586
00:35:12,080 --> 00:35:17,000
I believe Phum will feel better one day.

587
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:22,280
Also, he has Peem now.

588
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:24,240
He should feel better soon.

589
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:27,000
But seriously, I really have to thank Peem.

590
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:28,840
Since Peem came into his life,

591
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,200
Phum smiles more often.

592
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:33,200
He laughs more,

593
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,240
and he seems happier.

594
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:42,080
I think that’s Peem’s special talent.

595
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:46,280
He can make those around him smile.

596
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:49,280
I’ve been hoping all this time

597
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:53,480
for Phum to have someone by his side,

598
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,280
just like me having you here

599
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,440
because family can’t always be our safe zone.

600
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:11,320
But I want to be both your safe zone and your family, babe.

601
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,160
There you go.

602
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:15,920
You’re smiling already.

603
00:36:16,160 --> 00:36:17,080
You already are.

604
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:17,800
Pardon?

605
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:21,360
Though I act unreasonable and don’t behave well sometimes,

606
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:24,600
if one day you feel you no longer want to be with me,

607
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,680
just tell me straight

608
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,880
because if you disappear,

609
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:33,680
I would be in so much pain.

610
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:36,440
Come on, babe.

611
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:38,320
Look at me.

612
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:39,600
I’m so crazy over you.

613
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:41,800
How could I dump you?

614
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,720
I love you.

615
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,440
I’m head over heels in love with you.

616
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:47,760
I love you a lot.

617
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:48,320
I love you a lot.

618
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:49,040
Stop it.

619
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:49,960
It’s embarrassing.

620
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:53,960
There’s nobody around.

621
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:58,720
Anyway, thank you

622
00:37:01,080 --> 00:37:04,480
for loving me, even when I’m not always adorable.

623
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:06,920
Come on, babe.

624
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:11,560
Your eyebrows, ears, nose, eyes, and mouth are all adorable.

625
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:13,280
So are other things about you.

626
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,920
I love you no matter what.

627
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:18,040
I love you, too.

628
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:20,280
Eh? “You”?

629
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:21,280
That one?

630
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:21,880
This one?

631
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:22,480
The tree?

632
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:23,520
Who is called “You”?

633
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:25,960
Who’s named like that?

634
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:29,920
Fang loves Tan.

635
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:32,120
Come on, say it again.

636
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:33,560
Say it loudly and clearly.

637
00:37:33,560 --> 00:37:34,240
One, two, three.

638
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:36,240
I said, Fang loves Tan.

639
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:36,720
Come on.

640
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:37,960
You weren’t loud enough.

641
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:38,920
I don’t like it.

642
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:39,800
Fine.

643
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:40,720
Fang loves Tan.

644
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:44,000
Oh, I’m blushing.

645
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:50,440
I’m so happy for your mom

646
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:52,840
for having such a cute son like you.

647
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:53,640
You’re exaggerating.

648
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:55,320
I’m not.

649
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:58,640
Alright. I’ll stop.

650
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,320
Tan loves Fang, too.

651
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:06,200
What?

652
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:07,200
I couldn't hear it.

653
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:08,720
Tan loves Fang, too!

654
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,200
I already know that.

655
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:12,320
Tan loves Fang!

656
00:38:12,320 --> 00:38:13,160
I already know.

657
00:38:13,440 --> 00:38:14,360
Love you too.

658
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:16,080
Alright. I won’t get too loud.

659
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:17,640
But I love you.

660
00:38:18,720 --> 00:38:19,320
I already know.

661
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:28,160
Let’s grab something to eat.

662
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:49,520
[Ticketing]

663
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:53,040
Ever been on a train before?

664
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:53,600
Nope.

665
00:38:54,560 --> 00:38:55,600
I was right.

666
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:56,120
Let’s go.

667
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:07,040
Come.

668
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:22,680
Smile.

669
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:27,640
Smile.

670
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:33,240
Move.

671
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:45,920
Say cheese.

672
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:46,440
Cheese.

673
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:49,560
What cheese?

674
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:50,960
One more time.

675
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:54,800
Cheese.

676
00:39:54,840 --> 00:39:56,520
Cheese.

677
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,640
What a forced smile.

678
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:06,480
Thanks a lot.

679
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:08,720
For?

680
00:40:09,640 --> 00:40:11,000
For staying by my side.

681
00:40:21,640 --> 00:40:23,600
Sit there. It feels cool.

682
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:30,200
Head out.

683
00:40:31,200 --> 00:40:31,760
What?

684
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:32,840
Move your face forward

685
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:35,520
and stick your tongue out.

686
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:37,400
What?

687
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:38,120
Come on.

688
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:38,920
Like a Golden Retriever.

689
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:42,960
Go “woof, woof.”

690
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:44,000
Woof, woof?

691
00:40:44,040 --> 00:40:44,720
Yeah.

692
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:46,240
How does that look cute?

693
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:00,920
We’ve finally arrived.

694
00:41:01,120 --> 00:41:02,000
It took forever.

695
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:03,080
My butt is achy.

696
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,720
That sounds like you’ve never been on a train.

697
00:41:06,760 --> 00:41:07,200
Come on.

698
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,600
It’s been a while for me.

699
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:24,800
Let’s take some rest for now,

700
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,640
and eat something later.

701
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:33,680
You have pretty good taste for choosing this hotel.

702
00:41:34,120 --> 00:41:36,200
At first, I thought I wouldn’t be able to sleep.

703
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:37,280
Why?

704
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:39,600
Is this room too ordinary for you to sleep?

705
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:40,960
I can sleep here.

706
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:42,440
It’s not bad.

707
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:44,360
I approve.

708
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:46,560
Okay.

709
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:11,400
Does my face look that adorable?

710
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:12,800
Why are you smiling when looking at me?

711
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:16,720
You’re closing your eyes.

712
00:42:17,280 --> 00:42:18,320
How could you know I’m looking at you?

713
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:20,240
I’m using my radar.

714
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,760
And when can your radar finally detect it?

715
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:25,960
Detect what?

716
00:42:27,120 --> 00:42:28,280
My feeling.

717
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:32,080
When will you finally know that I love you?

718
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:43,880
Let’s go.

719
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:44,600
Let’s find something to eat.

720
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:46,200
Hold on.

721
00:42:48,760 --> 00:42:50,000
You haven’t given me your answer.

722
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:52,760
I thought I did. Can't you tell?

723
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:54,520
I can’t.

724
00:43:02,920 --> 00:43:03,960
This side, too.

725
00:43:07,640 --> 00:43:08,840
Let’s eat.

726
00:43:08,880 --> 00:43:09,360
I’m hungry.

727
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:10,560
Hold on.

728
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:11,200
Phum.

729
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:15,520
Stop.

730
00:43:16,480 --> 00:43:17,320
I’m hungry.

731
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:23,520
Let’s eat later.

732
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:06,920
Whoa.

733
00:44:07,360 --> 00:44:08,600
Lots of food.

734
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:11,960
You’re hungry. Eat a lot.

735
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:14,120
Eh? You aren’t eating?

736
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:15,960
I’m allergic to seafood.

737
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:17,120
Huh?

738
00:44:18,080 --> 00:44:18,960
Why are you confused?

739
00:44:19,440 --> 00:44:20,240
We’re at the sea,

740
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:21,240
so we must eat seafood.

741
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:22,440
Don’t worry.

742
00:44:22,720 --> 00:44:23,960
I’ve already ordered what I can eat.

743
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:25,720
This is not a big deal for me at all.

744
00:44:25,760 --> 00:44:26,840
I can pay.

745
00:44:27,640 --> 00:44:28,760
So, I won’t hold back then.

746
00:44:29,680 --> 00:44:30,640
Go ahead.

747
00:44:34,480 --> 00:44:35,160
Yummy?

748
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:36,800
To the max.

749
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:42,920
Do you want some?

750
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:50,480
Peem, smile.

751
00:44:57,880 --> 00:44:59,720
It’s nice traveling like this with you.

752
00:45:01,440 --> 00:45:02,920
I must thank you for bringing me.

753
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:09,680
Phum, can you ride a horse?

754
00:45:11,960 --> 00:45:12,560
Of course.

755
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:14,000
Why?

756
00:45:14,560 --> 00:45:15,280
Do you want to ride it?

757
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:17,680
Well, I do.

758
00:45:17,880 --> 00:45:18,800
But I guess I shouldn’t.

759
00:45:18,840 --> 00:45:19,280
I’m scared.

760
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:20,680
You have me here with you.

761
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:23,040
You don’t have to be scared.

762
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:24,360
You want to ride a horse, right?

763
00:45:24,840 --> 00:45:25,600
I’ll handle it for you.

764
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:27,680
Phum, don’t.

765
00:45:27,720 --> 00:45:28,840
Phum, come back here.

766
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:29,600
Don’t.

767
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:31,280
Why?

768
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:33,360
You said you wanted to ride a horse, didn’t you?

769
00:45:34,040 --> 00:45:35,000
Uh-huh.

770
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:36,920
He won’t bite you.

771
00:45:37,360 --> 00:45:38,280
Touch him.

772
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:44,440
Ride it.

773
00:45:46,120 --> 00:45:46,480
Hurry up.

774
00:45:46,520 --> 00:45:47,200
Don’t be scared.

775
00:45:52,520 --> 00:45:53,960
Hold this.

776
00:45:54,240 --> 00:45:55,480
Step here.

777
00:45:58,040 --> 00:45:59,000
Slowly.

778
00:45:59,240 --> 00:46:00,160
Don’t be scared.

779
00:46:02,080 --> 00:46:02,760
Are you ready?

780
00:46:03,680 --> 00:46:04,160
Yeah.

781
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:12,920
I feel like I’m a prince

782
00:46:13,240 --> 00:46:15,320
with a servant walking a horse for me.

783
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:17,840
Someone like you as a prince?

784
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:18,840
Why?

785
00:46:19,200 --> 00:46:20,440
Why can’t I?

786
00:46:21,600 --> 00:46:22,640
Annoying.

787
00:46:22,800 --> 00:46:23,760
Should I let go?

788
00:46:23,960 --> 00:46:24,440
Stop.

789
00:46:25,680 --> 00:46:26,800
Don’t let go.

790
00:46:28,320 --> 00:46:29,080
Fine.

791
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:29,960
I know that.

792
00:46:30,160 --> 00:46:31,280
Who would do that to you?

793
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:32,040
Right?

794
00:46:46,400 --> 00:46:47,200
Beautiful, isn’t it?

795
00:46:52,240 --> 00:46:53,840
Why did you bring me to the sea?

796
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:55,560
I don’t know.

797
00:46:55,840 --> 00:46:58,000
I just thought this place could make you feel better.

798
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:08,000
Don’t you want to know what happened to me?

799
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:13,240
If you want to talk about it, I know you will.

800
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:26,240
Actually, I argued with my dad.

801
00:47:33,840 --> 00:47:34,800
You know what?

802
00:47:35,520 --> 00:47:37,560
When I was a kid, I never wanted to study abroad.

803
00:47:40,320 --> 00:47:41,960
Even now, I still don’t understand

804
00:47:43,440 --> 00:47:45,960
why Dad sent me to study abroad alone.

805
00:47:48,320 --> 00:47:49,560
What’s more,

806
00:47:50,840 --> 00:47:52,920
I wondered why Mom didn’t object to it even once.

807
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:59,560
Back then, I was alone and isolated.

808
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:03,400
I cried every day.

809
00:48:07,440 --> 00:48:11,480
But luckily, Fang always called me,

810
00:48:14,880 --> 00:48:16,320
consoling me

811
00:48:17,800 --> 00:48:19,480
and keeping me company so I wouldn’t cry

812
00:48:21,840 --> 00:48:23,520
despite such a big timezone difference.

813
00:48:24,840 --> 00:48:27,000
He always called me.

814
00:48:27,760 --> 00:48:29,920
He woke up to talk to me no matter how late it was.

815
00:48:32,200 --> 00:48:33,600
But things aren’t the same anymore.

816
00:48:35,600 --> 00:48:37,760
No matter how much Dad tries to approach me

817
00:48:38,640 --> 00:48:40,240
and talk to me now,

818
00:48:41,840 --> 00:48:43,200
I still feel distant.

819
00:48:44,280 --> 00:48:46,520
The more he tries to approach me,

820
00:48:48,280 --> 00:48:51,480
the less I want to stay there.

821
00:48:58,480 --> 00:48:59,080
Peem.

822
00:48:59,920 --> 00:49:00,360
Yeah?

823
00:49:04,160 --> 00:49:05,440
Can I hug you?

824
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:19,240
I can’t remember the last warm hug I got.

825
00:49:21,120 --> 00:49:23,120
Why are you thinking about that last hug?

826
00:49:23,480 --> 00:49:25,000
Just focus on the hug you’re getting now.

827
00:49:35,560 --> 00:49:36,720
I’m sorry, Peem.

828
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:40,360
I’m sorry for treating you badly.

829
00:49:41,920 --> 00:49:43,040
Apology accepted,

830
00:49:44,200 --> 00:49:45,360
but I won’t forgive you.

831
00:49:48,440 --> 00:49:51,440
I’ll wait and check on your behavior first.

832
00:49:55,560 --> 00:49:58,400
Stop making that sad puppy face, Puppy Phum.

833
00:49:58,960 --> 00:50:00,480
Hey, cheer up.

834
00:50:02,040 --> 00:50:03,080
What are you doing?

835
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:04,600
My hair is a mess now.

836
00:50:06,080 --> 00:50:08,000
You’re a puppy.

837
00:50:11,120 --> 00:50:12,200
You already did very well.

838
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:21,920
Thank you for everything.

839
00:50:25,240 --> 00:50:27,400
Thank you for brightening my life.

840
00:50:58,680 --> 00:50:59,280
What?

841
00:51:31,440 --> 00:51:33,200
Are you two already dating?

842
00:51:33,200 --> 00:51:33,640
Uh-huh.

843
00:51:34,360 --> 00:51:35,200
Don’t feel slighted.

844
00:51:35,240 --> 00:51:36,920
Our couple will celebrate like them soon.

845
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:41,760
I have something fun to offer.

846
00:51:42,280 --> 00:51:43,240
To get back at him.

847
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:44,360
He made you his servant.

848
00:51:44,440 --> 00:51:45,120
Huh?

849
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:46,560
Peem is Phum’s servant?

850
00:51:46,600 --> 00:51:48,840
I think Toey has probably spread fake news already

851
00:51:48,880 --> 00:51:49,520
Huh? What?

852
00:51:49,520 --> 00:51:50,880
You need to speed up to win his heart.

853
00:51:50,920 --> 00:51:51,640
What should I do?

854
00:51:52,200 --> 00:51:53,400
You’re asking the right person.
